Large language models (LLMs) are a type of artificial intelligence that can understand, generate, and respond to human language in a natural and context-aware way. These models are trained on vast amounts of text data from the internet, books, and other sources, allowing them to learn patterns, grammar, and semantics across a wide range of topics.

